12/12/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- An increase in Bulgarian participation in NATO's operation in Afghanistan was the focus of talks between Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev and the NATO Combined Forces Command-Afghanistan chief, Lieutenant General Karl Eikenberry, who visited Sofia on Monday (December 11th). Stanishev said that Bulgaria would continue contributing actively to the stabilisation and reconstruction of Afghanistan and that in 2007, Sofia planned to deploy an additional mechanised unit there. On Tuesday, Stanishev is making an official visit to Iraq. (Sega - 12/12/06; Bulgarian Government website, Mediapool - 11/12/06)
